# Setup Instructions

## Prerequisites
- Python 3.8 or higher
- MQTT broker (Mosquitto recommended)
- Git

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
#git clone https://github.com/yourusername/iiot-simulation.git
cd iiot-simulation#
2. Create a virtual environment:
#python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate#
3. Install dependencies:
#pip install -r requirements.txt#

  ## Running the Simulation
1. Start your MQTT broker (e.g., Mosquitto)
2. Run the OPC UA to MQTT bridge:
#python scripts/opcua_mqtt_bridge.py#

3. In a separate terminal, run the visualization: #python scripts/data_visualization.py#

  ## Configuration
You can modify the simulation parameters in each script file or create a configuration file.
  #
